description: The Seoul Sculpture Festival is held in the Open City Park to promote Seoul as a city of sculpture. This year, an outdoor exhibition will be held, with a total of 18 artists participating in the Seoul Sculpture Award winning works and director invitation exhibitions. It has become an exhibition hall for art to breathe, an opening ceremony to announce the beginning of the sculpture city, a sculpture playground to maximize the appreciation of works, and street performances.
